member.name: F:Microsoft.VisualStudio.Shell.Interop.__VSPROPID4.VSPROPID_ActiveSolutionLoadManager
member.summary: Gets or sets an object representing the active Solution Load Manager. The default is null. A solution load manager is able to control how projects are loaded during the Solution Open operation. It can control whether projects are loaded immediately, loaded in the background (at idle), left to be loaded if needed, or stay unloaded. A solution load manager is expected to implement . A common approach is to have the solution load manager package autoload for the , for example [ProvideAutoLoad(UIContextGuids100.SolutionOpening)]. This property may also be set during or during for the pre-solution section.
